  "time_ut": 1661941931,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf \u0db6\u0daf\u0dd4 \u0dc6\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d91\u0dc5\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d85\u0daf\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Mahindananda pulled out the tax file",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna MP Mahindananda Aluthgamage said in Parliament today (31) that a major paddy mill owner in Sri Lanka who earns a net profit of 100 billion rupees in two seasons pays only 900,000 rupees in tax per year.",
        "The MP also said that the owner of that V mill has made a net profit of 50 billion in one season.",
        "Mr. Mahindananda Aluthgamage mentioned that he has bought 5 lakh metric tons of rice in a season and has sold it at 220 rupees and has made a profit of 70 rupees per kilo.",
        "Mr. Aluthgamage questioned where the Income Tax Department is when things like this are happening.",
        "The Income Tax Department has sent a letter to him asking him to pay 10 billion and he has sent a letter to the Income Tax Department saying that he cannot pay it. Mr. Mahindananda Aluthgamage said.",
        "Mr. Aluthgamage said that a liquor licensee earns a net profit of 15,200,000 per month, but pays only 2 or 3,000,000 in taxes per year. A gas station owner pays only 50,000 or 68,000 in taxes per year.",
        "Joining the debate on the interim budget, Mr. Mahindananda Aluthgamage said that if the country's revenues are properly managed, there will be no need for the IMF."
      ],
